(secondQuint)Study Protocol/ Registry of MultiPoint Pacing in Brazil.

 Any patient receiving a market-approved SJM Quadra Assura MP (CRT-D) or newer model quadripolar device with MPP capability and who meets the inclusion criteria and none of the exclusion criteria is eligible for enrollment in the study.

 Patients will be followed for 12 months after implant.

 Data will be collected after device implant (up to 30 days after successful implant), at 3, 6 and 12 months post-implant and during unscheduled visits.

